# Lucy Infrastructure & Deployment Context

## Where Lucy Runs

**Lucy is NOT running on your laptop. It runs on a Contabo VPS.**

- **VPS IP**: `167.86.82.46`
- **SSH**: `ssh -i ~/.ssh/id_lucy_vps root@167.86.82.46` (or `ssh contabo-lucy` via `~/.ssh/config`)
- **App directory**: `/opt/lucy/app` on the VPS
- **Service**: `systemctl status lucy` (systemd, auto-starts on boot, auto-restarts on crash)

## How to Deploy

```bash
git push origin main
```

That's it. This pushes to **both** GitHub and Contabo simultaneously:
- `origin` push URL 1: `https://github.com/ojashyadav101/lucy.git`
- `origin` push URL 2: `ssh://contabo-lucy/opt/lucy/repo.git`

The bare repo at `/opt/lucy/repo.git` has a `post-receive` hook that:
1. Pulls latest from GitHub (`git fetch origin main && git reset --hard origin/main`)
2. Runs `pip install -e .`
3. Runs `systemctl restart lucy`

Lucy is live ~10 seconds after push.

## Checking Logs

**Always check VPS logs, never your laptop:**

```bash
ssh contabo-lucy "journalctl -u lucy -f"               # live tail
ssh contabo-lucy "journalctl -u lucy -n 100 --no-pager" # last 100 lines
ssh contabo-lucy "journalctl -u lucy -p err -n 50 --no-pager" # errors only
```

Deploy hook log: `ssh contabo-lucy "tail -20 /var/log/lucy-deploy.log"`

## VPS Services

| Service | How to check |
|---|---|
| Lucy | `systemctl status lucy` |
| PostgreSQL | `docker ps` (lucy-postgres container) |
| Qdrant | `docker ps` (lucy-qdrant container) |
| OpenClaw gateway | `ps aux \| grep openclaw` (port 18789) |
| ClawRoute | `systemctl status clawroute` |

## Production `.env`

Lives at `/opt/lucy/app/.env` on the VPS. **Not in git.** Key production values:
- `LUCY_DATABASE_URL=postgresql+asyncpg://lucy:lucy@localhost:5432/lucy`
- `LUCY_OPENCLAW_BASE_URL=http://127.0.0.1:18789`
- `LUCY_QDRANT_URL=http://localhost:6333`
- `LUCY_ENV=production`

To update production env:
```bash
ssh contabo-lucy "nano /opt/lucy/app/.env && systemctl restart lucy"
```

